Pitcairn Appoints Laurie Ressin Martin as Managing Director & DC Office Head
Sep 24 15
Pitcairn has appointed Laurie Ressin Martin as managing director in its relationship management discipline, leading the company’s Washington, DC team. She will report to Averill Jarvis, managing director of client services and head of all of Pitcairn’s relationship teams, effective October 5. As the head of the Washington, DC office, Ms. Martin will manage Pitcairn’s growth initiatives in the DC market. She will oversee the delivery of investment and family office services to a growing group of multi-generational families, including developing, implementing and monitoring long-term financial plans, focused on asset allocation, portfolio management, and tax planning that meet clients’ short-term and long-term objectives.


